# Medusa Marketplace Project Structure

This is a **PetRescue Brasil** marketplace built on Medusa v2 framework for pet adoption platform.

## Core Architecture
- **Backend**: Medusa v2 with custom marketplace module
- **Storefront**: Next.js 15 (app router) in Portuguese (pt-BR)
- **Vendor Dashboard**: React + Vite for pet protector management
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17 with Redis for caching

## Key Directories

### Backend Structure
- [medusa-config.ts](mdc:medusa-config.ts) - Main configuration with environment validation
- [src/modules/marketplace](mdc:src/modules/marketplace) - Custom marketplace module
- [src/api](mdc:src/api) - API routes (admin, store, vendor endpoints)
- [src/workflows](mdc:src/workflows) - Business logic workflows
- [src/jobs](mdc:src/jobs) - Background job processing
- [src/subscribers](mdc:src/subscribers) - Event handlers

### Frontend Structure
- [storefront](mdc:storefront) - Next.js storefront for adopters
- [src/vendor-dashboard](mdc:src/vendor-dashboard) - React dashboard for pet protectors
- [src/admin](mdc:src/admin) - Medusa admin customizations

### Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Local development setup

## Environment Variables
Required variables are validated in [medusa-config.ts](mdc:medusa-config.ts):
- `DATABASE_URL` - PostgreSQL connection
- `REDIS_URL` - Redis for caching (production only)
- `JWT_SECRET`, `COOKIE_SECRET` - Authentication secrets
- `STORE_CORS`, `ADMIN_CORS`, `AUTH_CORS` - CORS origins

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run seed:petrescue` - Seed Brazilian cities and sample data
- `npm run test:integration:http` - Test critical API endpoints